iliar with the history, culture, and dynamics of the Service-including its biases, internal alliances and rivalries, self-image, folklore, and rhetoric. The book will prove indispensable for environmental and governmental specialists and for general readers seeking an in-depth analysis of one of America’s most admired federal bureaus.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNational parks and reserveszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aNational parks and reserveszUnited StatesxManagementxHistory. 0aNatural resourceszUnited StatesxManagementxHistory. 0aNature conservationzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014366940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300143669423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300143669/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles